  <prompt>
    Validate Phase A's 4 exit criteria are met (per spec §Success Criteria / plan.md §7
    Acceptance Criteria). Produce the Phase A exit-gate document recording green/red per
    criterion + evidence file references. After this task, request user sign-off before
    Phase B can begin (per project CLAUDE.md §Confirmation Triggers — "Any phase exit gate
    requires user sign-off").

    The 4 exit criteria:
    1. Chat-agent tool list driven by `sprk_analysistool` rows with
       `AvailableInContexts ∋ "Chat"` (validated by Pillar 2 tasks 006-013).
    2. Persona is a Dataverse-driven scope (`sprk_aipersona`); tenant override changes
       chat agent voice without code deploy (validated by Pillar 1 tasks 001-005).
    3. One generic `invoke_playbook` chat tool exists; `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` +
       `InvokeInsightsQueryTool` removed (validated by Pillar 3 tasks 020-023).
    4. `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` routes through `PlaybookExecutionEngine` (no
       alternate-key lookup) (validated by Pillar 4 tasks 024-025).

    Cross-cutting checks per spec §7:
    - BFF publish size ≤+5 MB total across R6 to date (sum of Phase A task deltas).
    - No new ADRs introduced (NFR-03).
    - Pre-fill flow signatures + 45s timeout + `useAiPrefill` UNCHANGED (NFR-07; Phase A
      should NOT touch pre-fill but verify zero impact).
    - All 11 node executors UNMODIFIED (NFR-08).
    - ZERO Microsoft Agent Framework references (NFR-04; grep evidence).
    - 4-channel PaneEventBus + 4-stage shell preserved (NFR-05, NFR-06).
    - Safety pipeline preserved (NFR-13).
    - All HIGH-severity CVEs resolved (per `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`).
    - All FULL-rigor tasks passed `code-review` + `adr-check` at Step 9.5.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    AI program manager + senior BFF engineer with R6 spec familiarity. Comfortable
    aggregating test/validation evidence across multiple task notes.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Phase A exit-gate document published at
    `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/phase-a-exit-gate.md` with
    green/red verdict per criterion + evidence-file references. User sign-off requested.
  </goal>

