  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: MINIMAL — exit-gate documentation rollup; no `.cs`".
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 028 ✅. Update `current-task.md` to task 029.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Collect Evidence">
      Gather task notes for 005 (Pillar 1 cutover), 013 (Pillar 2 batch validation), 023 (Pillar 3 closeout), 025 (Pillar 4 orchestrator refactor), 028 (Phase A vertical slice).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Verify Exit Criterion 1 — Data-Driven Tool List">
      Confirm task 013 evidence shows chat-agent tool list resolves from `sprk_analysistool` rows with `AvailableInContexts ∋ Chat`. Reference evidence file paths.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Verify Exit Criterion 2 — Data-Driven Persona">
      Confirm task 005 evidence shows persona resolves from `sprk_aipersona`; tenant override changes voice without code deploy.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify Exit Criterion 3 — Generic invoke_playbook + Bridge Removal">
      Confirm task 021 + 022 + 023 evidence: generic tool exists; specialized bridges deleted.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Verify Exit Criterion 4 — PlaybookExecutionEngine Routing">
      Confirm task 025 evidence: orchestrator invokes engine; no alternate-key lookup in chat /summarize path.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Run Cross-Cutting Audits">
      (a) Aggregate Phase A publish-size deltas: sum + verify ≤+5 MB R6 budget. (b) Grep `Microsoft.Agents` across all Phase A modified files: 0 results expected. (c) Verify NFR-07 pre-fill flow untouched. (d) Verify NFR-08 11 node executors untouched. (e) Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`: 0 HIGH-severity CVEs.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Author Exit-Gate Document">
      Write `notes/phase-a-exit-gate.md` with: green/red verdict per criterion + evidence references; cross-cutting check results; final recommendation (READY for Phase B / NOT READY).
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="🛑 Confirmation Gate — Phase A Sign-Off">
      PAUSE per project CLAUDE.md §Confirmation Triggers (phase exit). Present exit-gate document; request user sign-off before Phase B can begin.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      After sign-off: update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 029 ✅. Phase A complete. Reset `current-task.md` to next phase's first task. Report Phase A closeout.
    </step>
  </steps>

